author: pburba
msg: (copy_causes_phantom_eol_conflict): Reproducing this issue is simpler than
this test initially implied; no copies or backport branches are required.
Simply, if a property changes on a file or directory, then the DAV update
report handler tells the client to get all the path's properties and for
it (the client) to figure out what has changed (which it doesn't do, hence
this issue).  So all we need to do to provoke this issue is to merge a
simple text *and* property change on a file with the svn:eol-style
property set on it, which is what this change does.  Also rename the
test description to more aptly describe the bug.
